- [reporters murmuring]

718
00:45:29.813 --> 00:45:31.148
Hello?

719
00:45:31.231 --> 00:45:32.608
<i>Are you there?</i>

720
00:45:32.691 --> 00:45:33.942
We're all listening.

721
00:45:34.735 --> 00:45:35.777
Go on.

722
00:45:37.070 --> 00:45:39.239
<i>Well. I guess you all heard.</i>

723
00:45:39.323 --> 00:45:41.658
<i>Celine Dumont will do anything
to shut this story down.</i>

724
00:45:41.742 --> 00:45:42.868
- Ms. Dumont.
- Get out.

725
00:45:42.951 --> 00:45:44.286
- The board is--
- Get out!

726
00:45:44.369 --> 00:45:45.871
[Kabir] <i>Why is Ms. Dumont
making these threats?</i>

727
00:45:45.954 --> 00:45:47.623
<i>What exactly is she trying to cover up?</i>

728
00:45:47.706 --> 00:45:50.918
[Martin] <i>We have strong evidence that
Ms. Dumont offered bribes...</i>

729
00:45:51.001 --> 00:45:52.628
[in French]
We need to leak the Ivanov story.

730
00:45:52.711 --> 00:45:56.673
<i>Alex asking favors of oligarchs.
That will get us out of this mess.</i>

731
00:45:56.757 --> 00:45:58.008
I warned you. Celine!

732
00:45:58.509 --> 00:45:59.718
I told you to stop!

733
00:45:59.801 --> 00:46:01.845
- I'm coming.
- <i>You've totally fucked us.</i>

734
00:46:02.721 --> 00:46:04.723
["Porcelain" playing]

735
00:46:14.233 --> 00:46:15.984
[no audible dialogue]

736
00:46:19.738 --> 00:46:21.740
[no audible dialogue]

737
00:46:26.245 --> 00:46:27.996
[Kabir. in English]
<i>So this cover-up you're alleging.</i>

738
00:46:28.080 --> 00:46:30.499
<i>you're saying Dumont worked directly
with the EPA?</i>

739
00:46:30.582 --> 00:46:32.793
No. not... not exactly.

740
00:46:32.876 --> 00:46:35.128
[Kabir] So. this is all just speculation?

741
00:46:35.212 --> 00:46:37.756
[camera shutters clicking]

742
00:46:38.924 --> 00:46:41.093
No. No. it's not.

743
00:46:41.927 --> 00:46:44.930
The deal was brokered
by lobbyist Martha Ellison.

744
00:46:45.013 --> 00:46:46.849
who kept a copy of the report.

745
00:46:47.641 --> 00:46:50.477
She then gave it to her son. Cory Ellison.

746
00:46:51.019 --> 00:46:55.023
who has chosen to step forward in
the interest of the victims of Wolf River

747
00:46:55.774 --> 00:46:57.818
and in support of Bradley Jackson.

748
00:47:02.739 --> 00:47:04.074
[music continues]

749
00:47:14.877 --> 00:47:18.505
[Yanko] <i>As UBN prepares to host the
Paris Summer Games. there's no word yet</i>

750
00:47:18.589 --> 00:47:22.593
<i>on who will lead the company following
the departure of Celine Dumont.</i>

751
00:47:22.676 --> 00:47:26.471
<i>The board is expected to choose
an interim CEO within the next few weeks.</i>

752
00:47:26.555 --> 00:47:30.142
<i>And as always.
we're thinking of Bradley Jackson.</i>

753
00:47:30.225 --> 00:47:33.270
<i>It's day 35 of her detainment in Belarus.</i>

754
00:47:43.655 --> 00:47:44.948
[Mia] Thought you'd be in Paris.

755
00:47:45.449 --> 00:47:46.575
No. uh...

756
00:47:47.409 --> 00:47:49.703
I'm on the red-eye tonight.

757
00:47:50.704 --> 00:47:54.541
We should grab dinner when you get there.
talk about Chris's development slate.

758
00:47:54.625 --> 00:47:57.794
Yeah. I know this great restaurant
in the 3rd arrondissement.

759
00:47:57.878 --> 00:48:00.464
Plastic tablecloths. judgy waiters.

760
00:48:01.340 --> 00:48:02.633
- You'll love it.
- [chuckles]

761
00:48:04.384 --> 00:48:06.303
Well. now that Celine is out.

762
00:48:06.803 --> 00:48:09.431
just gonna be you and me
keeping this place afloat.

763
00:48:09.515 --> 00:48:12.100
Yep. You and me. once again.

764
00:48:12.726 --> 00:48:14.478
- I'll see you in Paris.
- Mm-hmm.

765
00:48:42.464 --> 00:48:46.343
[Celine] <i>Miles. forgive me
for leaving without saying goodbye.</i>

766
00:48:48.637 --> 00:48:50.305
<i>I thought it might be easier.</i>

767
00:48:51.390 --> 00:48:53.016
<i>for both of us.</i>

768
00:48:53.100 --> 00:48:55.644
[in French] Dad said he'll meet you
at the Cap-Ferrat house.

769
00:48:56.687 --> 00:48:58.063
- Not at the office?
- No.

770
00:48:58.146 --> 00:48:59.273
It's crawling with lawyers.

771
00:48:59.356 --> 00:49:00.858
as you can imagine.

772
00:49:03.193 --> 00:49:04.528
- Is there a problem?
- No.

773
00:49:04.611 --> 00:49:05.821
No problem.

774
00:49:08.365 --> 00:49:11.451
[Celine. in English] <i>My father will make
me the scapegoat for all of this.</i>

775
00:49:12.578 --> 00:49:17.040
<i>He'll throw me to the wolves
and watch them devour me.</i>

776
00:49:23.213 --> 00:49:24.339
Alex?

777
00:49:24.923 --> 00:49:26.341
Yes. I'm in the kitchen.

778
00:49:26.967 --> 00:49:30.387
- I'm just heading out. What's going on?
- Hey. Uh. uh. I just... [chuckles]

779
00:49:31.555 --> 00:49:34.641
I would just feel better if I knew exactly
what you are walking into.

780
00:49:35.434 --> 00:49:37.186
[stammers] I'm fine. I'll figure it out.

781
00:49:37.269 --> 00:49:38.896
And what if this thing falls apart?

782
00:49:38.979 --> 00:49:40.814
It won't. It's not gonna fall apart.

783
00:49:41.815 --> 00:49:43.400
You still haven't spoken to Bradley?

784
00:49:45.319 --> 00:49:48.071
- No. not directly.
- And no one has laid eyes on her?

785
00:49:48.155 --> 00:49:49.615
- No.
- Alex. Alex...

786
00:49:49.698 --> 00:49:51.033
I could come with you.

787
00:49:51.116 --> 00:49:53.452
I could come with you.
I could be there on the ground

788
00:49:53.535 --> 00:49:55.913
in case this thing goes sideways.

789
00:49:57.039 --> 00:49:59.249
Given that
the feds are basically hands-off--

790
00:49:59.333 --> 00:50:02.503
Listen. I really appreciate the offer.
but you have done plenty.

791
00:50:02.586 --> 00:50:04.796
Really. This is on me now.

792
00:50:04.880 --> 00:50:08.008
And I'm not... I'm not going to leave
that airport without her. I'm not.

793
00:50:10.469 --> 00:50:12.638
It's the coming back part that
I'm worried about.

794
00:50:17.226 --> 00:50:20.062
You afraid I'm gonna steal the keys
to your GV and move to Bali?

795
00:50:20.145 --> 00:50:21.146
Yeah. Right.

796
00:50:21.230 --> 00:50:22.606
But then who would drag me

797
00:50:22.689 --> 00:50:25.984
into these highly
compromising international incidents?

798
00:50:26.068 --> 00:50:28.362
Yeah. I think I've been enough of a pain.

799
00:50:31.156 --> 00:50:32.866
Well. I'm developing a tolerance.

800
00:50:37.913 --> 00:50:38.914
[sighs]

801
00:50:41.542 --> 00:50:42.835
I gotta go.

802
00:50:54.096 --> 00:50:56.932
I owe you for all of this.

803
00:51:05.357 --> 00:51:06.441
Let's call it even.

804
00:51:10.404 --> 00:51:11.697
Yeah. Okay.

805
00:51:12.197 --> 00:51:13.907
[elevator dings]

806
00:51:23.959 --> 00:51:25.460
[both sigh]

807
00:51:59.745 --> 00:52:02.122
All set. The security team
is letting us run this.

808
00:52:02.789 --> 00:52:04.041
- It's time.
- Okay.

809
00:52:19.348 --> 00:52:21.350
[breathing heavily]

810
00:52:41.912 --> 00:52:44.915
[gentle music plays]

811
00:52:44.998 --> 00:52:47.000
[gasps. breathes heavily]

812
00:53:01.056 --> 00:53:03.600
[breathing shakily]

813
00:53:09.064 --> 00:53:10.899
[sobbing]

814
00:53:12.025 --> 00:53:14.027
[breathing heavily]

815
00:53:15.070 --> 00:53:17.072
[sobbing continues]

816
00:53:21.785 --> 00:53:23.787
[Alex] It's okay. I got you. I got you.

817
00:53:23.871 --> 00:53:25.539
Thank you for coming to get me.

818
00:53:27.165 --> 00:53:28.959
I'm sorry I fucked it all up.

819
00:53:29.042 --> 00:53:30.669
[Alex] No. you didn't.

820
00:53:30.752 --> 00:53:33.297
I was wrong. The story's out there.

821
00:53:33.380 --> 00:53:34.506
You don't understand.

822
00:53:35.090 --> 00:53:36.633
You changed everything.

823
00:53:37.509 --> 00:53:38.635
- I did?
- Yes.

824
00:53:38.719 --> 00:53:40.512
Let's get you home.

825
00:53:44.266 --> 00:53:45.350
You're okay.

826
00:53:46.305 --> 00:54:46.793
